description:
Inquiring minds want to know the answer to that question. Rumors abound: Was she murdered by the worldwide Bolshevik revolution? Is she the unwilling victim of diabolical mind control experiments? Did evil Martians kidnap her? Or is she living out her existence as a mindless vegetable? Sandi Shore continues her quest to find the answer.

1. The Queen of Kalamazoo

2. The People's Choice
name: The Queen of Kalamazoo

description: Black Ops Operative Dameon Spikes is on his way to Washington, D.C., where his commanding officers will brief him on his new mission…his first new orders since the attack of several destructive bombs enhanced with an infectious, biochemical disease changed the landscape of the country. In transit, Spikes soon finds himself surrounded and being overcome by a horde of zombies. Just when there appears to be no way out, Spikes receives assistance from a rather unlikely source…
name: Zombanation Wars

description:
You'll Have That follows the lives of Andy and Katie, a newlywed couple in their twenties, as they try to figure out life together.

In the first published volume of the webcomic strip You'll Have That, newlyweds Andy and Katie battle noisy neighbors, have an unpleasant restaurant visit, and cope with the everyday struggles of married life. Foreword by Jef Mallett, creator of the syndicated comic strip, Frazz.
name: Vol. 1

description:
You'll Have That is an online comic strip that follows the lives of Andy and Katie, a newlywed couple in their twenties, as they try to figure out life together.

In the second volume of the popular webcomic strip, Andy defaces the ceiling with a golf club, Steve falls in love, and Katie won’t open her Christmas presents early. Foreword by Bruce Blitz, host of the Emmy-nominated TV series Cartooning With Blitz.
name: Vol. 2

description: Originally featured in STAR SPANGLED COMICS #7-32 (1942-1944), The Newsboy Legion stars a group of scrappy boys who fight crime in their home of Suicide Slum. Watched over by adult hero The Guardian, The Newsboy Legion battles crime through their own newspaper, taking on crooked politicians, slum lords, fifth column agents and much more.

volume.name: The Newsboy Legion by Joe Simon & Jack Kirby

description: Not familiar with the hilarious web comic strip, You'll Have That? Well now's your chance to get acquainted with everybody's favorite newlywed couple, Andy and Katie, in this 32-page one-shot published by Viper Comics! The strips in this book were published in 2006 and were hand-picked by regular readers of the online strip!

Samurai Cat in the Real World

description:
Aphrodite IX Trade Paperback collects issues #1-4 of the series of the same name as well as the hard to find issue #0 plus incredible bonus art by Marc Silvestri (Civil War: The Initiative, Hunter-Killer), Joe Benitez (Supergirl), and Michael Turner (Superman/Batman, Ultimate Wolverine). Aphrodite IX is the perfect weapon, only she doesn't know it. She's programmed to kill and then erases all memory of her mission and her former life, like a reset button was hit in her mind. Now the ideal assassin wants to know who programmed her and she won't stop until she finds out!

The deadly and beautiful cyborg Aphrodite IX is the perfect assassin. She kills without retaining memories of her past. But she questions, and begins the search for her true identity, leading to more and more blood...

Featuring an oversized all-new story and reprinting the classic Peter David and Dale Keown tale from INCREDIBLE HULK #393!

description: The Flash and Red Raven join up with the rest of the Teen Hellions for a major battle! With Beast Grrl, Starfire, Tempest, and Cyborg by their sides, they prepare for the return of Raven's evil Dad. How evil? 6,000-year-old-demon-from-Azarath evil! Will they be ready?
name: The Teen Hellions, Part Two

description: Things sure get real horrorshow in the second chapter of Al Columbia (Biologic Show) and Ethan Persoff's (Top Notch) black comedy, The Pogostick. There are Haitian zombies and voodoo warlords, a cancer patient, a butcher knife, sudden unemployment, the disadvantages of caller I.D., a horrible death, a cuckoo's nest revisited, cops with guns and flashlights, an ambulance, fat garbage bags, a clean apartment, and the gentle flow of blood on a carpet...all in two glorious colors.
name: Issue Two

description:
Issue one introduces us to Snail, who lives in a tree with his best friend, Tom the Bug. We also meet Eppie - a fairy-like creature, and the object of Tom's affections.

Also includes the story "Count Stinkenpuss", in which the title character has his cat stolen and flies to Mount Kilimanjaro in a bid to rescue him.

Things Just Get Away From You collects all of Holcombe's late-1990s comics work, with a bonus new story, "Hails at Sea," thrown in for good measure.

Things Just Get Away From You leads off with "King of Persia," a 1001 Nights/Yiddish vaudeville-inspired graphic novella in which king Faisal Al-Ghazali must win the affection of the woman he loves by traveling to an enchanted land in search of a giant emerald, while accompanied by his faithful companion, the talking camel, Jamila.

From the pages of Holcombe's short-lived but beloved comic book series Poot come four stories: "Swollen Holler," a romance between two bugs whose supporting characters include an elderly bachelor, Professor Owl, and a lonely snail named Snail; "The Eighth Wonder," a breezily suggestive, picaresque pantomime story featuring a romantically-inclined barrel-clad wanderer; "The Red Grampus," in which the whaler captain Reginald Nubbins pursues an old enemy unleashed upon him by his first great love, the mysterious Julietta; and "Count Stinkenpuss," in which the eponymous count wins the prestigious Tattersall Cat Show, only to have his prize-winning cat, Mr. Lovely, stolen by a vengeful ex-lover, resulting in a battle to the death in a dogfight over Mt. Kilimanjaro.

The book also includes "What Do Pretty People Think About?," a pathetic bit of speculative envy in which Holcombe muses about the condition of physical beauty: What do pretty people think about? Do pretty people feel pain like normal people? Do pretty people even have souls? Finally, the all-new "Hails at Sea" is a collage of Holcombe's troubled dreams over a three-year period. Vampires, unfortunate sexual metaphors, talking fish and Tiny Tim all make an appearance in this tribute to the return of the repressed.
name: Things Just Get Away From You

volume.name: Things Just Get Away From You

description: Issue three is the odd one out in the series, telling an independent, single-issue story. The adventures of Snail and Tom continue in Poot #4.

In the final issue of the series, we find out whether Tom the Bug and Eppie will ever get together.

Also contains the short piece "This Revisionist History Bugs Me", by Penny Van Horn.

description: When Andy is given a surprise gift by his grandmother, no one is more surprised than the toys in his room... it's a second Buzz Lightyear! The stage is set for a Star Command showdown as only one Buzz can stay... but when the wrong Buzz is returned to the store, Woody and the other toys must mount a rescue mission! Collecting the TOY STORY Ongoing issues #0-3.
name: TPB/HC

volume.name: Toy Story: The Return of Buzz Lightyear

description:
Lynda Barry's previous book, the Eisner Award-winning What It Is, explored the question 'Do you think you can write'? Now with Picture This, Barry asks 'Why do we stop drawing?' and 'Why do we start?' It features the return of Barry's most beloved character, Marlys, and introduces a new one, the Nearsighted Monkey. Picture This is an inspirational, take home extension of Barry's traveling, continually sold out, and sought after workshop, 'Writing The Unthinkable.'

The near-sighted monkey book
name: HC

person_credits.name: Lynda Barry
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Jason knew earthquakes had been causing tremendous difficulties for nearby Shimmer City, but, hey, that's not his problem-- or at least it wasn't. You see, while the seismic activity was destroying buildings and sending the city's citizens into a general panic, it was also unearthing a mysterious mechanized giant, one with a cockpit perfectly sized for a kid like Jason! Now Jason has more than just a robot pal, he has a responsibility to protect his home and his family from alien criminals like GoGo Diablo who see the quake-ridden metropolis as ripe for the picking! It's more mechanized madness by J. Torres (Sidekicks, Copybook Tales) and Mike Norton (The Waiting Place, G.I. Joe)!

volume.name: Terry and the Pirates Color Sundays

description:
Lyn loses her leg in an automobile accident, after feeling sorry for herself she quickly recovers when she meets Sheri who teaches her all she needs to know about Amputee Love.

Adult comic.

Even 25 years after her death, Rubi Fields, America's most popular movie star, still has the nation enthralled -- and obsessed! Is that obsession somehow linked to a chain of violent events in Beacon City? How does this Rubi-mania factor into Ivor Wynne's presidential campaign? Where is Rubi's lovechild? And what really happened to Rubi Fields? The pieces to this twisted puzzle all fall into place in the surprising conclusion of The New Frontier!

1. Idol Worship

2. The Rubi Fields Story
name: Idol Worship

description: After a small scale nuclear war throws society into a tailspin, four friends are struggling just to survive on a day to day basis. Complicating matters is that one of them is destined to be the wielder of a Darkstar, one of six mystical weapons instrumental in the final fate of mankind. When Cain, an ancient vampire who wants the weapon for himself starts stalking them, the only thing that can save them is Vanessa, another vampire who wants to use the Darkstar to destroy Cain. Caught between two vampires with an age old grudge, the world crumbling around them and other things that go bump in the night, day to day life becomes a constant struggle for survival.

In the wake of Hurricane Katarina, 100 comic creators joined forces to create an anthology to benefit the victims of the hurricane and subsequent flooding of New Orleans. The anthology collects 36 stories and seven pinups, and will find its way into the comic stores in summer 2007. With stories ranging from frist reactions to the catastrophe, slice of life, humor, horror, the supernatural and superhero fun, original tales as well as those featuring existing characters by various creators, HOPE: New Orleans is a book catering to all tastes in genres. The proceeds from the sale of this book will go toward the Southeast Louisiana Chapter of the Red Cross and its continued effort to help the victims of the Hurricane Katrina.

Softcover, 220 pages, B&W.
name: GN
